title: Arctic broadband satellites complete key tests ahead of mid-2024 launch
summary: Two satellites designed to bring mobile broadband coverage to the Arctic region for civilians and military users have completed key tests ahead of their planned launch next summer.

title: Satellite imagery reveals explosion at China’s Jiuquan spaceport
summary: A Chinese launch vehicle maker appears to have suffered an explosion at a test site at Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center.

title: Defense and intelligence contractor Arcfield acquires Orion Space Solutions
summary: Arcfield, a U.S. defense and intelligence contractor, announced Nov. 29 it has completed its acquisition of Orion Space Solutions, a developer and manufacturer of small satellites and sensor payloads.

title: Firefly conducts first Miranda engine test
summary: Firefly Aerospace has conducted the first hot-fire test of a new engine that will power the company’s future launch vehicles.

title: New RL10C-X Rocket Engine To Debut On Vulcan In 2025
summary: United Launch Alliance (ULA) and Aerojet Rocketdyne have announced a revamped version of the 60-year-old RL10 rocket engine called the RL10C-X will make its inaugural flight on the Vulcan Centaur rocket in 2025.

title: Firefly Set to Launch Lockheed Martin Tech Demo In December
summary: Firefly set to launch their next Alpha rocket in December, carrying Lockheed Martin Electronically Steerable Antenna Payload Tech Demo

title: NASA Delays Dragonfly Mission To Titan
summary: The Director of NASA’s Planetary Science Division has announced a one-year delay in the launch of the Dragonfly mission to Saturn’s moon Titan.

title: Industry group opposes White House mission authorization proposal
summary: An industry group says it is opposed to a White House proposal for regulating novel space activities, arguing it could be burdensome and confusing for companies and agencies.
